On Escalation Ticket # 00427058 the new comment has been added: Robert Zavalczki:

It looks like the user hasn't enabled the Network Extension. They can do this either manually by clicking "Allow" on the "allow network extension" prompt or through a deployment or Mobile Device Management software (such as JAMF, for example)

Also, while we expect to report the Gmail email sender at all times, the email receiver will not be available for attachments and when editing a draft that doesn't have a recipient. FYI: @WaitingOnEngineer

On Escalation Ticket # 00427058 the new comment has been added: Robert Zavalczki:

This is not an issue. The customer attached a confidential file that was blocked.

As I've said in my comment earlier in this thread, the sender and recipients are not supposed to be sent for attachments and when
 editing a draft that doesn't have a recipient.

They will appear though when the customer adds confidential information in the email body or subject.

Also the customer did not upgrade to the latest version, but to 5.9.4.0.


FYI: @WaitingOnEngineer
